[2026-07-05 09:16:45] darwin: cycle 71 -- optimized file_guard.el symlink check. In my-gptel--guard-check-write and my-gptel--guard-check-append, added has-symlink boolean (not (string= expanded truename)). When has-symlink is nil (common case -- no symlink), the truename predicate call is skipped, avoiding a redundant funcall that would test the same string against the same predicate. When has-symlink is t (symlink detected), both expanded and truename are checked as before. Also updated docstrings to document the symlink behavior. The error fallback (condition-case on file-truename) sets truename=expanded, making has-symlink=nil, so only the expanded check runs -- equivalent to old behavior where the truename check would run on expanded (redundant). Reviewer found 0 CRITICAL, 0 MAJOR, 3 MINOR (has-symlink slight misnomer for .. normalization -- safe direction; code duplication between write/append -- pre-existing; docstring wording -- acceptable). All 483 tests pass. Committed e0eb34b, pushed to remote.
